* [[Эдгар Аллан По]] - писатель, поэт<ref group=p>''Life and Letters and the London Mercury: An International Monthly of Living'', Published by Brendin Pub. Co., 1929 (v.2 1929 Jan-Jun, p.171): "Poe, like Nietzsche, was a manic-depressive; and his existence followed a comparable course."</ref><ref group=p>From the ''Collected Works of Edgar Allan Poe'' by Thomas Ollive Mabbott, Eleanor D Kewer, Maureen C Mabbott, Page 561, Belknap Press of Harvard University Press, 1969: "Poe certainly had manic and depressive periods"</ref><ref group=p>from ''Edgar Allan Poe: Rhetoric and Style'' by Brett Zimmerman, published by McGill-Queen's Press - MQUP, 2005, (quote, from p.177: "...when the former was in one of his black moods - evidence supporting (in part) the theory that Poe was manic-depressive (see also Ostrom 404, 437)" [http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=OKxwOqUgNvkC&pg=PA177&dq=poe+manic&lr=&sig=ACfU3U0wnRt1FJa5t1vsp-ChYZnFQ7Uu1g]</ref>
